{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 77,
  "title": "第七十七章（天道）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "天下之道，猶張弓者也。高者抑之。下者舉之。有餘者損之。不足者補之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故：天之道，損有餘而益不足。人之道，損不足而奉有餘。"
    },
    {
      "text": "孰能有餘而有以取奉於天者？唯有道者乎。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以：聖人為而弗有，成功而弗居也。若此，亓不欲見賢也。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天道暗昧，舉物類以為喻也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 12,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言張弓和調之，如是乃可用耳，夫抑高舉下，損強益弱，天之道也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 26,
          "end": 26
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天道損有餘而益謙，常以中和為上。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 26,
          "end": 26
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人道則與天道反，",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 26,
          "end": 26
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "世俗之人損貧以奉富，奪弱以益強也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 19,
          "end": 19
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言誰能居有餘之位，自省爵祿以奉天下不足者乎？唯有道之君能行也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 27,
          "end": 27
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人為德施，不恃其報也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 27,
          "end": 27
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "功成事就，不處其位。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 44,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不欲使人知己之賢，匿功不居榮，畏天損有餘也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "與天地合德，乃能包之，如天之道。如人之量，則各有其身，不得相均，如惟無身無私乎，自然然後乃能與天地合德。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言唯能處盈而全虛，損有以補無，和光同塵，蕩而均者，唯其道也。是以聖人不欲示其賢以均天下。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
